Class UserManager

java.lang.Object
com.example.cab302simplestock.model.UserManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
IUserManager
public class UserManager extends Object implements IUserManager
Implementation of the userManager interface using a userDAO for the managing of users. Uses dependency injection to get the user DAO.

      Adds a new user to the database, all values for the User should be set, except for the ID value which is set by the database.

    • updateUser

      public void updateUser(User user)
      Updates an existing user in the database, every value should be set in the User parameter. The user in the database will have every single value overwritten by this method. Any empty value set in the parameter will overwrite the old value with an empty value.
      Specified by:
      updateUser in interface IUserManager
      Parameters:
      user - The user with its values to update. The ID must be set for the database to find the user.

    • deleteUser

      public void deleteUser(User user)
      Deletes a user from the database, only the ID value for the user to delete needs to be set. If this method is called it should be assumed the user is gone and unrecoverable.
      Specified by:
      deleteUser in interface IUserManager
      Parameters:
      user - The user to delete. Only the ID needs to be set, as the database uses the ID to find the user.
